e of exponential expansion, intermediate\nviscosities give rise to compact colonies with \"fingers\" that are ripped away\nto break into smaller cell clusters, and at the lowest viscosity, the expanding\ncolony breaks up into many genetically-diverse, mutually repelling, island-like\nfragments of yeast colonies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 23 Dec 2018 23:51:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-03"}
