f portable and\nlow-cost MRI systems. It is aimed to familiarize the readers with relevant\nknowledge, literature, and the latest updates of the development on permanent\nmagnets for MRI. Perspectives on and challenges of using permanent magnets to\nsupply a patterned magnetic field, without spatial-linearity nor high\nhomogeneity, for reconstruction in a portable setup are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Dec 2018 12:51:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-31"}
